replies.bodyText:
Yes, exactly.
I am probably nitpicking here but I would probably capture the webflowOrder field into a new WebflowAutoConfigurationProperties class to be used by everything else, and I would then just reference that as a nested field:
    @NestedConfigurationProperty
    private WebflowAutoConfigurationProperties webflow = new WebflowAutoConfigurationProperties();
It might be pre-mature; I am thinking we might want to reserve the spot for WebflowAutoConfigurationProperties for additional settings that might be introduced in the future but it would very well be overkill. Your call.
